         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Roughly dressed ossuary has inner ledge on two sides and flat lid. Inscription appears on the chest's right side in large lettering. Tzaferis interprets it as the initials of the deceased. Similar inscriptions appear on two other ossuaries found on Mount Scopus' western slope (see inscriptions "jeru0122" and "jeru0183").</p>
         </div>
